survey_response.review_text: We had been consulting Dr. Ranjana ever since we planned our pregnancy and we are glad we took this decision. Her advice and medication has been extremely beneficial through out the period. Any words of appreciation will be less for the kind of advice, strength and support that she has provided us in all these months. Not only is she an expert in her area but is also very approachable, friendly and patient. She has always been available and responded to all our queries even in the wee hours. She goes an extra mile to understand the problems of her patients and provides the best solution. Our pregnancy wasn't a very smooth one but Dr. Ranjana ensured we were calmed down every time we panicked. Even during the delivery process she was available at all times and ensured that the baby was delivered safely without causing any risk to the mother or the baby. On 16th of October 2020 we were blessed with a baby boy and we are thankful to Dr. Ranjana as it wouldn't have been possible without her support. we would definitely recommend Dr. Ranjana to all the future parents to be.

review_reply.reply_text:
As per Online Consultation Guidelines framed by Govt of India, one can prescribe online medications ONLY with a  diagnosis of reasonable surety  based on a "good patient history " . With inconsistent symptoms  which are open to many causes, blind prescription of medication online is NOT allowed. 
Patients need to understand that Online Consultation is NOT  SUBSTITUTE to chamber consultation and clinical examination  is  sometimes an essential prerequisite to  prescribing medicines. Moreover, prescribing any ointment based on vague symptoms is NOT GOOD OR ETHICAL PRACTICE. 
Hence the patient comment on a doctor's experience or confidence without proper knowledge of the subject shows her immaturity. 
Anyway , I wish you all the best for the future
